						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rājakēśarivarman, Year 13 = c. 10th Century.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of 20 kaḻañju of gold, through the body called <hi rend="italic">Paṉṉiraṇḍunāṭṭu-perumakkaḷ</hi>, by the lady Kāmakkanār, wife of Iḷangōnaḍikaḷ, for feeding 20 Brahmanas on the day of <hi rend="italic">ēkādasi.</hi> The gift was to be administered by the body called <hi rend="italic">Tiruvēkādasi-gaṇapperumakkaḷ.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> Vol. XIII No. 232.]</p>						

